sting institutions (especially the BBC). Additionally, the study discusses the films he made for the cinema and considers some of the ways in which Garnett's experiments in film technology - 16 mm in the 1960s, digital video in the 1990s - have shaped his creative output.Tony Garnett will be of interest to all levels of researchers and students of British television drama, media and film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRealism on television. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aBritish television drama.  aCathy Come Home.  aThis Life.  aTony Garnett.  aUp the Junction.  aWorld Productions.  acreative producer.  adrama series.  aexecutive producer.  asocial realist aesthetic.1 aLacey, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779435240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847794352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847794352/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles